description: Class Description This class is perfect for brand new beginners, dancers of other styles, or more experienced dancers that want to continue to improve technique. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 8:00- 9:00pm No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!

Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Monday from 8:00- 9:00pm Must have instructor permission to attend. No partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!

description:
We are excited to bring you dancing the 2nd Saturday of every month right in the heart of downtown, with a wooden dance floor!!!!! 8:15pm Doors open
Salsa Caliente’s team will be there to greet you. 8:30pm Salsa lesson
Taught by World Salsa University certified instructor, Christina Morrison. No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson so you will already know a LOT of people by the time the dancing begins. 9:30pm- midnight
Dancing to Salsa, Bachata, Merengue, Cha Cha Cha and more. Ages 16+ welcome. CASH ONLY at the door. $15.00 per person. Tickets available at the door or on Eventbrite. There will be a small non-alcoholic concession available as a fundraiser for the teams. *Limited capacity. First come first served. We reserve the right to refuse entrance at the door.
location: STUDIO 4 ATHLETICS, 715 YATES ST, Langley, BC, CA

All ages welcome. $15.00 per person + service fee on Eventbrite or cash only at the door. $13 cash for Edelweiss Club members at the door only. *Limited capacity. First come first served. event_name: Sunday Sundown Social: Salsa Fire, Bachata Desire, Kizomba Inspire
description: A vibrant Latin dance social by the ocean with a 4:00–4:30 PM beginner lesson (no partner needed) followed by social dancing from 4:30–7:30 PM featuring Salsa, Bachata, Kizomba, and Merengue. Doors open at 3:45 PM. Cover: $5 students, $10 general (cash only).
location: Songhees Plaza (near the Johnson Street Bridge), Victoria, BC V9A, Canada, Langley, BC, CA

dance_style: bachata, cha cha, dance, merengue, salsa
description: Dancing the 4th Friday of every month at an all ages venue right in the heart of downtown, with a wood dance floor. 7:45pm Doors open. 8:00pm Salsa lesson. 9:00pm- midnight Dancing to Salsa, Bachata, Merengue, Cha Cha Cha, Bolero & Latin Hustle. All ages welcome. Limited capacity. First come first served. We reserve the right to refuse entrance at the door.
location: 117 St. Lawrence ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8V1X7, CA
price: $15.00 per person + service fee on Eventbrite or cash only at the door. $13 cash for Edelweiss Club members at the door only.

event_name: Sunday Sundown Social: Bachata Temptation, Salsa Sensation
description: Beginner-friendly Intro to Bachata lesson (4:00–4:30 PM) with Sebastian & Hannah, followed by an open-air social featuring Salsa, Bachata, Kizomba, and Merengue at Songhees Plaza by the ocean.

event_name: Rest&Resonate: an Evening of Restorative Yoga and Live Music
description: Join Anna & Roxie for a dreamy candlelit evening of restorative yoga, live music, and guided journalling. Facilitated by Roxie Fehr of Across the Water | Yoga Anna Bigland-Pritchard of ABP Music Studio | Music. The space will be dreamy, there will be tea, guided journalling, poetry, restorative yoga shapes that can be adapted for any body, and LIVE MUSIC! Anna will be playing guitar, creating dreamy sound worlds with vocal looping, and singing you lullabies all evening.
location: Little Fernwood Gallery. 1923 Fernwood Ave., Victoria, Langley, BC, CA

event_name: Sunday Sundown Social: Salsa Fire, Bachata Desire, Kizomba Inspire
description: Beginner-friendly Intro to Kizomba lesson from 4:00–4:30 PM, followed by open-air social dancing with Salsa, Bachata, Kizomba, and Merengue from 4:30–7:30 PM at Songhees Plaza by the Johnson Street Bridge. location: Songhees Plaza (near the Johnson Street Bridge), Victoria, BC, Canada, Langley, BC, CA

event_name: Sunday Sundown Social: Salsa Fire, Bachata Desire, Kizomba Inspire

event_name: West Coast Swing in the Square
description: Come join BC Swing Victoria for a fabulous (and FREE) evening of fun and West Coast Swing dancing at Centennial Square! The schedule for the night will be: 6pm (sharp) there will be an intro lesson to West Coast Swing. 7 - 9pm WCS music will be provided by DJ Carolyn Gebbie. Note: For those who are familiar with the 2019 WCS Rally routine, and would like to practice performing it live prior to Sept 7, the 'Hands Up' song will be played at 7:30 and 8:30pm. There will be WCS instructors on hand to answer questions about WCS or how to improve your WCS dancing.
location: Centennial Square, Victoria, British Columbia, Canada, Langley, BC, CA

description: Victoria WCS Collective Tuesday dances. $7 at the door - cash or etransfer. Free for dancers registered in a series of WCS lessons. Door opens at 7:30pm. DJ's in the comments. Beginners are welcome. No partner is required. There will NOT be a beginner lesson, but if you're brand new, let the person at the door know and they'll find someone to teach you the starter steps. Dance shoes or socks on the dance floor only. Bring your own water. No food or drink (except water) in the dance area by request of the hall. If you bring a snack to keep your energy up, please enjoy it in the foyer.
location: 3255 Harriet RD, VICTORIA, BC, V8Z3S3, CA

dance_style: dance, swing, wcs, west coast swing
description: Come join us every Saturday all year long for a fabulous WCS social dance from 8 - 11pm. Just $10 for the ($5 for students). Meaghan Efford and Bob Gebbie 's lesson on June 1st (starting PROMPTLY at 7pm) will be the only lesson in June, and it will be a great way to build, refresh or accelerate your skills in the dance, so please be sure to take advantage of this opportunity.
location: BC Swing Dance Club Victoria, Langley, BC, CA

description: Join us for a magical summer night of salsa, bachata & merengue under the sunset at the Ukrainian Cultural Centre! Intro class at 8:00 PM, social dancing from 8:30 PM until 11:59 PM. Dress in tropical sunset-inspired attire. Late entry $15 at the door.
location: Ukrainian Cultural Centre, 3277 Douglas St., Victoria, BC

description: Sunday Swing at Logan's is BACK! Quick 15min beginner swing lesson at 8:30pm, social dancing from 8:45pm to midnight. 19+.

description: Join Saanich in celebrating the 58th annual Strawberry Festival. description: The Soul Shakers are an in-demand band and undoubtedly one of the best dance bands on Vancouver Island! Top-notch musicianship, stellar harmonies and high energy performances are a trademark of this fine band led by powerhouse singer and entertainer Joyce 'the voice' Allensen. This band will have you singing and dancing along to classic popular Soul, Motown and R&B tunes as well as many other popular tunes. The Soul Shakers also feature music from their two independently released albums Love Is Love (2015) and Ready For You (2019). Get ready to feel the joy of a Soul Shakers performance! You won't leave the dance floors! The Upstairs Lounge is a licensed restaurant and bar, doors open at 6 pm for dinner service, the band starts playing at 7:30 pm.
location: Upstairs Lounge, Oak Bay Recreation Centre 1975 Bee Street Oak Bay, BC V8R 5E6

description: Class Description This class is perfect for brand new beginners, dancers of other styles, or more experienced dancers that want to continue to improve technique. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 8:00- 9:00pm No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!
location: 725 Yates ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8W1L6, CA

event_name: Hot Pot with Bu Von Blume
description: Join us for a sizzling hot pot feast with Bu Von Blume - it's gonna be lit! Disco Dance, Funk Frenzy, Hip-Hop Party, Soul shaking and even sneaky Ska skanking July 12th at the Phoenix Bar. HOT POT is a gaggle of baddies that bounce in the space between Jazz, RnB, Reggae, Funk, Soul, Hip-Hop, and other genres of black music from this hemisphere, enhanced with a strong Asian flavour. They love laying down a feral groove and busting out moves with the crowd, almost as much as they love talking about themselves in third person. And Bu Von Blume? Six piece, fully interactive, 100% original, silly as heck, audience engaging, funk, disco, ska, cumbia, balkan, punk, soul, hip-hop, whatever-as-long-as-it’s-danceable super fun-time flower-power horn driven dance and theatre band.
location: Phoenix Bar and Grill, 3944 Quadra Street Victoria, BC V8X 1J6

description: Class Description This class is perfect for brand new beginners, dancers of other styles, or more experienced dancers that want to continue to improve technique. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 8:00- 9:00pm No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. event_name: Salsa On 2 & Cha Cha Cha - Intermediate/ Advanced
description: Class Description This class is for experienced dancers and performers that want to continue to push themselves with more complex techniques. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both.
